  {
    "id": "transfer-characteristic",
    "type": "plotly",
    "title": "Open-Loop Transfer Characteristic",
    "description": "Because the open loop gain A_vd is so massive (e.g. 100,000), a difference of less than a millivolt between the inputs is enough to drive the output all the way to the supply rails.",
